# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using pyenv and micro-services.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different OS, they may break the lock.
#   pipenv run pip freeze > requirements.txt is preferred.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains specific versions of dependencies
#   poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains specific versions of dependencies
#   pdm.lock

